args: Oh yeah, I'm in perfect form today.\nMy axe feels light as a feather!
Well, if it ain't Cleo!\nTime for lunch already?
Uh oh. Ya got yer serious face on.\nDid I eat all the ham again?
You were appointed as Saint Lotier's\nlieutenant by your father, yes?
That's my understandin' of it, yeah.
And the prince also asked me to be\na commander in our forces.
Normally a serious job like that would\nget a big fat ＂no way＂ from me, but I said\nI'd do it, so I been trainin' and—
Ranzal, listen to me. I know it's important\nto refine your combat skills, but I think you\nshould focus on something else first.
Ya kiddin' me? Look at this bod!\nI'm hotter than two rats sleepin'\nin a wool sock!
I am referring to your ATTIRE, you cad.\nIf you mean to take these positions,\nyou need clothing suited to your rank.
I dunno. I'm pretty comfy in this getup.
And yet there will be occasions where your\ncurrent mode of dress is not...suitable.
If you appeared at an official function\ndressed like that, for example?
You wouldn't just be shaming yourself—\nyou would be shaming your father and\n{player_name} as well.
Well, I have said my piece.\nI will let you decide how to proceed.
Well, hell. Probably can't be showin' up\nin front of a buncha blue-bloods in this.
Thing is, I got nothin' else to wear.
...But I know just the guy to talk to!
Hey, Malka! I need a favor!
Let me guess: You want your armor\nrepaired again.
Nope. I actually need some NEW armor.
Heya, Ramona! Didn't see ya there.
I just popped by to get input on some\nmaterials. Couldn't help overhearing\nyou're looking for new armor?
You know it. I'm movin' up in the world,\nso I need me some better duds.
If that's what you are looking for,\nyou have come to the right man.
So then! What kind of armor do you seek?\nI will take any and all requests.
Gimme somethin' sturdy AND flashy!\nLike a butterfly with nunchucks, yeah?
I wanna be covered from head to toe\nin metal so thick it'll repel anything.
But THEN I want ya to use five colors of\ndragon scales so shiny they blind anybody\nwithin, say, a mile radius.
This new position of yours must be...\nquite something.
I just need all them fancy folks to think\nI know what the hell I'm doin'.
Did somebody else just walk in here,\nor were ya yellin' at me?
I've repaired enough armor in my day;\nI know how people fight in it.
You, for example, don't use heavy armor.\nInstead, you wear only a minimum amount\nof metal to cover particular areas.
That allows you to approach enemies\nquickly and wield your heavy weapon\nwith speed and grace.
I knew ya knew about this stuff, but I\ndidn't know ya KNEW knew. ...Ya know?
Indeed—and I would shame myself and\nall craftsman if I made armor that was\ninappropriate for its wearer.
Even if said armor was purely ornamental\nand used for diplomatic purposes.
Yet here you are asking for nonsense like\nhead-to-toe armor and dragon scales.
The materials are one thing, but I simply\nrefuse to make anything that will hinder\nyour movement.
Would you really turn your back on\neverything you've stood for until now?
Are you going to use your new position as\nan excuse to laze about in the rearguard\nand let others fight for you?
Because I'd rather die than forge armor\nfor a fighter like that.
I ain't some fancy noble what's gonna\nsit around eatin' fish egg sandwiches or\nwhatever while my men fight'n die!
No, that doesn't sound like you.
Yeah, well...sorry 'bout all the yellin'.\nYa just got under my skin for a second.
I don't blame ya for gettin' angry, Malka.\nI see where yer comin' from.
Anyway, just forget I asked about\nany of this, yeah?
If you AREN'T planning to turn your back\non your style, that changes everything.
You require armor beautiful enough to fit\nyour new position, but functional enough\nnot to limit your movement.
Then I will make you the finest armor\nI can that fits those requirements.
My only condition is that you leave the\nspecifics to me. Are we agreed?
Hell yeah, we're agreed! I ain't much for\nthinkin' about stuff anyway.
Then please look forward to the results.
Sounds like we have our work\ncut out for us.
I take it I can count on you to help\nwith the materials?
Of course—but in return, I want a favor.
Hey! Is my armor really done?!
It certainly is. Take a look.
This is even better than I thought!
Of course. Let me help you into it.
Hmm... Looks like the size is just right.
Yeah, it don't feel tight at all.
Heh. I see you found it already.
It's not as flashy as your first request,\nbut I think it really suits you.
Hey, I said I was sorry about that whole\n＂blindin' dragon scale＂ thing.
And I am only teasing you.
Anyway, why don't you take this\nto go with it?
Think of it as a congratulations gift\nfrom me for your new position.
Don't worry—it is simple and elegant,\nand will fit your style of combat to a T.
Huh... Feels like it's almost an\nextension of my arm.
She helped me with all the materials\nneeded to craft your armor.
But she also proposed making that sword,\nwhich I helped her craft.
Man, I really owe ya both.
Oh, but we weren't the only ones\nwho aided in your request.
My sisters helped to forge the sword.
Also, your armor is based on a design\nfrom Alberia's founding.
Nicolas and Althemia dug up the\ninformation on that front.
Oh, and Francesca tracked down a\nrare metal used to fortify the armor.
Just about everyone in the castle\nsaid they wanted to help.
That's how much everyone here trusts you.
So you had better live up to those\nlofty expectations, sir.
Ya put yer hearts into makin' this stuff,\nand I'm gonna use it to open up a great\nfuture for New Alberia!
